
Aim:

To implement a C++ class template along with a pure virtual function inside an abstract base class, and demonstrate runtime polymorphism with templates.
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Algorithm:

1. Start the program.
2. Create an abstract base class template using:
template <class T> class Base
3. Inside the class, declare a pure virtual function such as:
virtual void display(T a, T b) = 0;
4. Derive a child class from the template base class and override the pure virtual function.
5. In the main() function:
Create a pointer of base class template type.
Create an object of derived class template.
Assign derived class object to base pointer.
6. Call the overridden function using the base class pointer to achieve runtime polymorphism.
7. Display the results.
8. End the program.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Program (C++ Pure Virtual Function with Template):

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

// Template Base Class with Pure Virtual Function
template <class T>
class Operation {
public:
    virtual void display(T a, T b) = 0;  // Pure virtual function
};

// Derived Template Class
template <class T>
class Addition : public Operation<T> {
public:
    void display(T a, T b) {
        cout << "Addition: " << a + b << endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    // Base class pointer using int
    Operation<int> *ptr;
    Addition<int> obj1;

    ptr = &obj1;
    ptr->display(10, 20);

    // Base class pointer using float
    Operation<float> *ptr2;
    Addition<float> obj2;

    ptr2 = &obj2;
    ptr2->display(3.5, 2.5);

    return 0;
}
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Output:

Addition: 30
Addition: 6
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Result:

The implementation of a pure virtual function within a template class is successfully demonstrated. The program shows how abstract classes, virtual functions, templates, and runtime polymorphism can be combined in C++.